<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4451092>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 62. Mycale (Kerasemna) humilis (Thiele, 1903), a–d, light microscopic images from histological slides of the holotype of Biemna humilis, ZMB 3203, from Ternate, Indonesia, a, algal strand encrusted by skeletal tracts and microscleres, b, detail of a, c, massed presence of toxodragmas in the tissue, d, microscleres, including sigmas, toxodragmas, anisochelae I (arrow I) and anisochelae II (arrow II), e–f, light microscopic images of ZMA Por. 16382 from Ambon, Indonesia, e, skeletal structure of algal strands and interconnecting spicule tracts, f, detail of e." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4451092/files/figure.png" .

